<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">033.4111 Eden, Anthony/1<hi rend="superscript">2/5</hi>
                            </note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                    State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-16">February 16,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The British Ambassador called at his request and said that Eden
                                expected to leave London for this country about the middle of next
                                week. I expressed special gratification at his coming and assured
                                him of the warmest greeting and welcome. I said we had no agenda or
                                program thus far but that we were now working on various phases of
                                such an arrangement. I stated that whatever we may develop I shall
                                be glad to acquaint him accordingly and that I hoped the Ambassador
                                in turn would do likewise with me.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>